(691, 18707, 'WAQAR', 'AHMED', '09/08/1979', 'WAQAR_AHMED_20151017_11-58-58.doc', 'waqarrajput@yahoo.com', '', 'Qatar', 'I am a Science Graduate with 13+ Years operational experience in different Oil & Gas & Petro-Chemical Processing Plants. More than 07 Years Amine Treatment and Sour Water Stripping Unit Experience including Erection, Pre-Commissioning, Commissioning and Start Up activities of Amine Treatment Unit (Sour Gas Treatment plant).\n\nI am currently working with Qatar Gas (Premier LNG Company)  3000 MMSCFD (gas, condensate and water)  Separate the products and deliver the gas to 02 LNG trains, remove H2S and stabilized condensate and Sour Water Stripping Unit remove H2S from waste water maintain pH of water Filter it and inject water back to Water Injection Wells.\n\nCONDENSATE TREATING Merichem caustic wash condensate treating process to convert mercaptans from the condensate stream into disulfide oil is to de-odorize the condensate.\n\nABU DHABI (UAE) Onshore oil Operation Company ADCO I had been active role n responsibilities for smooth execution of all FFD project activities n development Like New CPF Facility Commissioning & Initial Start-Up , New Oil well Flow line Commissioning Tie-in activities and making sure of compliance of PTW system.\n\nBefore this I worked with BHP Billiton Australian Based Oil And Gas Company , Tullow oil Pakistan (dev) Ltd (Multinational Oil & Gas Company & Fauji Fertilizer Company performed duties in Gas Processing Plants, Amine Gas Sweetening, Dehydration plant As Plant Operator. I had actively participated in the Erection, Pre-Commissioning, Commissioning and Start Up activities of Sour Gas Treatment plant. The said plant consist of Amine Sweetening Unit (H2S removal system using MDEA), Dehydration Unit (using Tri-Ethanol Glycol)and Sour Water Treatment Unit. Plant is equipped with the DCS Centum CS 3000 by YOKOGAWA & SCADA system. Active member of the ERT (Emergency Response Team). \n\nIn Fauji Fertilizer Company (Petrochemical Plant) as Process Operator 05 years Experience and worked on Ammonia Plant(expansion unit) DCS TDC-3000. Pakistan Largest Ammonia Urea complex.The capacity of ammonia plant is 1100 T/D.Plant process is Haldor Topsoe, designed and constructed by Snamprogetti. I worked on the following units. \nGas Purification (Desulphurization), Reforming Section, Secondary Reformer, Shift Conversion, Process Waste Heat Boiler, AMINE TREATMENT UNIT Acid Gas Carbon Di Oxide CO2 Removal unit( Using MDEA),Low Pressure Steam Boiler, Methanation, Catalysts loading, Chemical Handling etc .\nGood Knowledge/experience of production operations in DCS, Fire & Gas Detection, PLC Operation and Auto ESD/ Blow down systems.\nGood mechanical aptitude and a basic knowledge of process instrumentation and DCS operations & Basic Computer skills. \nI will leave no stone unturned by worth to fulfill the requirements of said position. My detail resume is attached. \n\nYours Sincerely, \n\nWAQAR AHMED \n\nDoha Qatar \nCell # +97455607212;', 1445111936, '178.153.107.112', 1),
