(2506, 18714, 'Niteesh', 'Dingare', '23/02/1963', 'Niteesh_Dingare_18714_20170108_01-04-25.docx', 'niteeshd@yahoo.com', '00971559493360', 'United Arab Emirates', 'Hello Sir / Madam,\n\nI am interested in the advertised job opening. Please note that I am not UAE national.\n\nI am a Chemical Engineer and have more than 25 years of experience in Process Design, Commissioning & Operations Support. Upstream Oil & Gas experience-14 years (10 offshore + 4 onshore), Petrochemical experience -11 years.   Offshore experience include Process Design of Offshore Production and Processing Facilities such as Offshore Wellhead Platforms, Production Platforms, Trunk-lines etc.  I am looking for a senior Lead level position in Process, Operations Support and Development fields. I have worked for both Consulting, EPC and Operating companies and have done conceptual studies, engineering proposals for tenders, basic / front-end engineering design, detailed engineering, pre-commissioning/commissioning of plant and day-to-day trouble-shooting of problems in plant. I have strong process optimization skills that has led to added revenue (by producing more oil with little or no investment) and cut operating costs by streamlining the operating equipment.  E.g. in my assignment with Dubai Petroleum, I managed to boost liquid production from wells by 17000 bpd by lowering the back-pressure and stopped one power generator, two pumps and was looking forward to stop two more power generators and two pumps without affecting the production. \n\nWhile working with McDermott, I also worked on two Enhanced Oil Recovery (EOR) projects.\n\nWhile working for McDermott, I have completed the work on Saudi Aramco LTA-2 -SAF-3 project till pre-AFC stage.  This work comprising 4 fields Safaniya, Marjan, Berri and Zuluf which included well-head platforms (including auxiliary platforms), tie-in platforms, on-shore facilities and pipelines. Work included both greenfield as well as brownfield work. With having a good grasp on the understanding of the project, I came up with various optimized configurations â€“some of which were accepted by Saudi Aramco â€“ prominently among them was changing flange rating of on-shore facility from 1500# to 900# rating which led to substantial saving both for my Company as well as Saudi Aramco. My team ensured that all the deliverables were issued within the given schedule. While working for McDermott, I had worked as a consultant for various Saudi Aramco projects including SAF-2 and Karan-45 project. I am well-versed in international engineering standards.\n\nI have good exposure to various international standards such as SHELL DEPs, British Petroleum standards, Saudi Aramco standards and Petronas standards. \n\nI had a short course in Incident Reporting, Investigation, Root Cause Analysis and close-out while working with McDermott. \n  \n                        Please note that I had worked in Dubai Petroleum as Senior Facilities Engineer which included the role as Operations Engineer. Given the opportunity, I will help your Company to operate facilities smoothly and efficiently and also help cut capital and operating costs by coming up with optimized configuration.  I am attaching my resume along with this mail for your consideration for the advertised position of Senior Facilities Engineer.  \n\n I am currently based in Dubai, UAE\n\nRegards,\n\n\n\nNiteesh Dingare', 1483866264, '86.97.130.50', 1),
