(18701, '16/2013', 0, 'Head of Finance (UAE Nationals Only)', '', 'General Manager', '', 'Finance', '', '   <h3>Job purpose</h3>	                     <p>To ensure effective management of the finance function as the organisation continues to develop in scale and complexity. The new Head of Finance will be a core member of the executive management team, reporting to the General Manager (GM).</p>                                          <h4>Key responsibilities:</h4>                                          <h3>Executive management</h3>                     <ul>                     	<li>Serve as a member of the executive leadership team.</li>                         <li>Participate in key decisions pertaining to strategic initiatives, commercial development, business development and operational transformation.</li>                         <li>Take ownership of the finance function and the financial performance of the business.</li>                         <li>Take ownership of the performance management processes.</li>                     </ul>                                          <h3>Financial control and budgeting</h3>                     <ul>                     	<li>Ensure robust budgeting and forecasting across the business; ensuring that all business discussions and decisions are fully analysed in terms of their financial implications.</li>                         <li>Oversee the preparation of the monthly management accounts and ensure that they are fit for executive management decision-making purposes as the business grows.</li>                         <li>Steer, oversee and measure the performance of billing to customers and suppliers.</li>                         <li>Review and improve existing financial systems and processes, leading the development, delivery and production of management information.</li>                         <li>Review and improve existing financial controls and risk management processes, driving changes and improvements as required.</li>                         <li>Review and improve budget discipline in the business, assigning and upholding budget responsibility and accountability.</li>                         <li>Oversee the production of the annual and interim financial statements, working closely with the GM.</li>                         <li>Provide support to the GM and other stakeholders as required in the preparation of Executive Management papers and other presentations, including trading updates.</li>                         <li>Lead the annual audit process, working closely and proactively with the external auditors.</li>                     </ul>', '', '<p>To ensure effective management of the finance funct ion as the organisation continues to develop in sca le and complexity. The new Head of Finance will be a c ore member of the executive management team, reporting to the General Manager (GM).</p>', '', '<h3>Executive management</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Serve as a member of the executive leadership team.</li>\n	<li>Participate in key decisions pertaining to strategic initiatives, commercial development, business development and operational transformation.</li>\n	<li>Take ownership of the finance function and the financial performance of the business.</li>\n	<li>Take ownership of the performance management processes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Financial control and budgeting</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Ensure robust budgeting and forecasting across the business; ensuring that all business discussions and decisions are fully analysed in terms of their financial implications.</li>\n	<li>Oversee the preparation of the monthly management accounts and ensure that they are fit for executive management decision-making purposes as the business grows.</li>\n	<li>Steer, oversee and measure the performance of billing to customers and suppliers.</li>\n	<li>Review and improve existing financial systems and processes, leading the development, delivery and production of management information.</li>\n	<li>Review and improve existing financial controls and risk management processes, driving changes and improvements as required.</li>\n	<li>Review and improve budget discipline in the business, assigning and upholding budget responsibility and accountability.</li>\n	<li>Oversee the production of the annual and interim financial statements, working closely with the GM.</li>\n	<li>Provide support to the GM and other stakeholders as required in the preparation of Executive Management papers and other presentations, including trading updates.</li>\n	<li>Lead the annual audit process, working closely and proactively with the external auditors.</li>\n</ul>', '', '<ul>\n	<li>Qualified chartered accountant with proven post qualification experience...</li>\n</ul>', '', 1, 'Dubai', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
