(1, 'SIMON CATTLE', 'General Manager ', '<p>Simon is the General Manager of Dubai Supply Authority (DUSUP) the business responsible for the procurement and management of natural gas supplies for the Emirate.</p>\r\n', '1e0b58d3a4f09e1bc7087e32684fa913.jpg', 1),
(2, 'Mohamed Hassan Al Hammadi', 'Chief Operating Officer (COO) ', '<p>Mohamed has been the Chief Operating Officer of Dubai Supply Authority since August 2015 and leads the Operations Division which ensures the delivery of Natural Gas safely and efficiently through the Dubai Network. With more than 30 years’ experience in the oil and gas industry, Mohamed has gained knowledge and expertise across a range of disciplines with major oil and gas companies; he spent 14 years with Abu Dhabi Marine Operating Company (ADMA OPCO), 7 years with Emirates General Petroleum Corporation (EMARAT) and 12 years with Dolphin Energy Limited.<br>\r\nMohamed graduated from West Glamorgan Institute of Higher Education, Swansea, UK in 1986 with Higher National Diploma in Engineering and Bachelor of Science in General Engineering.</p>', 'mohamed.jpg', 2),
(3, 'Jeremy Hardwick', 'Chief Commercial Officer (CCO) ', '<p>Jeremy is the Chief Commercial Officer of Dubai Supply Authority (DUSUP) and is responsible for leading the commercial and functional activities across the DUSUP organisation. Jeremy joined DUSUP in October 2010 to lead the start-up and development of the LNG import business for Dubai. Jeremy has over 30 years, experience in the oil and gas industry holding a number of Gas Commercial, Functional and Engineering roles in BP, Conoco and British Gas.<br>\r\nJeremy graduated from the University of Leeds, UK in 1984, with a BSc in Mechanical Engineering. He gained an MBA from the University of Newcastle Upon Tyne, UK in 1991.</p>', 'jeremy.jpg', 3),
(4, 'T A Mathews', 'Chief Finance Manager ', '<p>Mathews joined Dubai Supply Authority as Finance Manager in May 2007 and was appointed to the role of Chief Finance Manager in 2015.<br>\r\nMathews is a Chartered Accountant with over 25 years’ experience in the Oil &amp; Gas and Banking sectors across the Middle East and Southern Africa. Prior to his business career Mathews served for 5 Years as a Commissioned Officer in the Indian Army. Mathews obtained a Bachelor of Science Degree from Bangalore University in 1978 and is a Member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India.</p>', 'mathews.jpg', 4),
(5, 'Pedro Amendola', 'Chief Technology Officer (CTO) ', '<p>Pedro is the Chief Technology Officer of Dubai Supply Authority (DUSUP) responsible for the delivery of the Engineering and Project Management of all of DUSUP’s infrastructure developments. Pedro joined DUSUP in January 2008 and has had a number of Project and Operational roles before his appointment as CTO in 2015.<br>\r\nPedro has over 30 years’ experience in the oil and gas industry and prior to joining DUSUP, Pedro has also served in a variety of Engineering and Management positions in the areas of Terminal, Pipeline and Projects working for Petrozuata and VEPICA in Venezuela.<br>\r\nPedro graduated from Universidad Simón Bolívar in Venezuela in 1986 with a Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering.</p>', 'pedro.jpg', 5);
